<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  cerby — bundled HTML export template.
  Renders a Markdown document as a single self-contained, shareable HTML file.
  Governed by references/html-export.md.

  Placeholders the exporter fills:
    {{TITLE}}    browser tab title (derive from the doc's first H1 or filename)
    {{CONTENT}}  the Markdown body converted to HTML
    {{SOURCE}}   source Markdown filename, e.g. postmortem.md
    {{DATE}}     export date, e.g. 2026-05-22

  Styling override surface: the :root block below. When a DESIGN.md exists at
  repo root, overwrite these custom properties with DESIGN.md tokens and change
  nothing else. With no DESIGN.md, ship this default as-is.
-->
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>{{TITLE}}</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg:        #fbfaf8;
    --ink:       #1f2937;
    --ink-muted: #6b7280;
    --accent:    #c2410c;
    --border:    #e5e0d8;
    --code-bg:   #f3f1ec;
    --font-body: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    --font-mono: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    --measure:   46rem;
    --radius:    6px;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html { -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .doc {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 2rem;
  }

  h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
    line-height: 1.25;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.25em 0 0.6em;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 1.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0.3em;
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.18rem; }
  h4, h5, h6 { font-size: 1rem; }

  p, ul, ol, blockquote, table, pre { margin: 0 0 1.1em; }

  a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

  ul, ol { padding-left: 1.5em; }
  li { margin: 0.25em 0; }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.88em;
    background: var(--code-bg);
    padding: 0.12em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  pre {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.9em 1em;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  pre code { background: none; padding: 0; font-size: 0.85em; }

  blockquote {
    margin-left: 0;
    padding: 0.2em 1.1em;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 0.94em; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0.5em 0.7em; text-align: left; }
  th { background: var(--code-bg); font-weight: 600; }

  hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 2em 0; }
  img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }

  .doc-footer {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  @media print {
    :root { --bg: #ffffff; }
    body { font-size: 11pt; }
    .doc { padding: 0; max-width: none; }
    .doc-footer { padding: 1rem 0 0; max-width: none; }
    a { color: var(--ink); }
    pre, code, th { -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; print-color-adjust: exact; }
    pre, blockquote, table, img { break-inside: avoid; }
    h1, h2, h3, h4 { break-after: avoid; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<main class="doc">
{{CONTENT}}
</main>
<footer class="doc-footer">
Point-in-time HTML snapshot of <code>{{SOURCE}}</code>, exported {{DATE}}. The Markdown file is the source of truth.
</footer>
</body>
</html>
